<div id="p627" class="blockpost rowodd firstpost">
	<h2><span><span class="conr">#1&nbsp;</span><a href="viewtopic.php?pid=627#p627">2009-07-28 09:50:45</a></span></h2>
	<div class="box">
		<div class="inbox">
			<div class="postleft">
				<dl>
					<dt><strong><a href="profile.php?id=90476">JosephDP</a></strong></dt>
					<dd class="usertitle"><strong>Member</strong></dd>
					<dd class="postavatar"></dd>
				</dl>
			</div>
			<div class="postright">
				<h3>DHT: LAN node discovery without tracker?</h3>
				<div class="postmsg">
					<p>Hi,<br /><br />I use bittorrent download on a LAN environment, for school and classrooms. I would like to see P2P LAN use to avoid use of WAN bandwith, as we install/download same package on several&nbsp; LAN computers.<br /><br />I would like to see a Bittorrent protocol to discover LAN peers, without need to use an external tracker, seeding... even without WAN connectivity. Maybe using DHT and some node discovering? <br /><br />I presume, from my very beginers point of view, that adding such functionality (LAN Peer) to DHT should be easy and very convenient on those LAN environment where I am sharing same file over several PC, so I can gain speed (no WAN use, or minimal) and reduce resources.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="clearer"></div>
			<div class="postfootleft"><p>Offline</p></div>
			<div class="postfootright"><div>&nbsp;</div></div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>

